column4: I have a problem with Ubuntu, possiblly some one here can assist me.
I have seen this before with  the eepro100 drivers and this machine.  I need it to load the e100 driver instead.  I cannot find the option in module.conf, where can I set this?
can you load the module with modprobe?
well, rmmod the one you don't want and modprobe the one you do want. see if it works
